  "prompt": "Can a person who is blind from birth dream?",
  "response": "Yes, people who are blind from birth can dream, but their dreams are different from those of sighted individuals. Since they have never experienced visual imagery, their dreams are primarily composed of other sensory experiences such as:\n\n1. Sound\n2. Touch\n3. Smell\n4. Taste\n5. Emotions\n\nSome studies suggest that people blind from birth have more vivid dreams involving non-visual sensory experiences. The content of their dreams is often richer in auditory, tactile, and emotional details compared to dreams of sighted people.\n\nThe parts of the brain typically associated with visual processing in sighted people are still active in people who are blind, but they are used for processing other sensory information, which contributes to their unique dream experiences.",
